<dl id="n36169g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36169g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36169g"> 169(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> after breaking a small / amount of stone</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[York Workhouse, Vagrant Ward]</font> Except those who come in on Saturday night, tramps are not detained for two days, but are liberated the morning after arrival, <mark>after breaking a small amount of stone</mark>. <small> B. Seebohm Rowntree, <a name="BSRP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BSRP"><cite title="source">Poverty, A Study of Town Life</cite></a>, 3rd ed.? (1922) 434</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
